I will omit diuers others for breuity; and although this may ſéeme no iuſt Exception againſt the Fathers, yet it ought to make vs cautious, how we truſt them to be the true Fathers; and not counterfeits: the rather for that the Papiſts, haue often alleaged ſuch counterfeit Fathers to credit their doctrine with. For proofe whereof, Torrenſis the Ieſuite citeth ſuch bookes for S. Auguſtines as are knowen and granted to bee none of his;
